<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 2:24PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Fergus
County through 300 PM MDT...
At 223 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Winifred moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fergus, Suffolk and Christina.
This includes Highway 191 between mile markers 22 and 33.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
